---
description: Enforce consistent image and avatar fallbacks across the app
alwaysApply: true
---

# Image Fallback Consistency

- For non-user entities (`club`, `tournament`, `event`, entity preview cards, notifications, thumbnails, hero blocks), use `EntityImage` or `TournamentThumbnail`.
- Non-user entities must fall back to the ball placeholder (`tournamentPlaceholder`) when the image is missing, invalid, or fails to load.
- Do not use raw remote `<Image source={{ uri: ... }}>` for clubs/tournaments/events unless there is a very specific reason and the same ball-placeholder fallback is preserved.

- For user entities (`profile`, `member`, `organizer`, `director`, `chat user`, `join request`, `notification user avatar`), use `RemoteUserAvatar`.
- User avatars must default to initials, not the ball placeholder.
- Always pass a meaningful `initialsLabel` when rendering a user avatar.

- If a screen shows tournament/club/event data in more than one place, check all dependent renderers too:
  lists, mini-cards, notifications, chat previews, modal context cards, hero/header blocks, and secondary tabs.
- If a UI pattern intentionally has no image slot, keep it image-less; do not assume the placeholder is already covered elsewhere.

## Examples

```tsx
// Non-user entity
<TournamentThumbnail imageUri={event.image} size={48} />
<EntityImage uri={club.logoUrl} style={styles.logo} resizeMode="cover" placeholderResizeMode="contain" />

// User entity
<RemoteUserAvatar
  uri={member.user?.image}
  size={56}
  fallback="initials"
  initialsLabel={member.user?.name ?? 'Member'}
/>
```
